All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Appointment
    This class creates the Appointment object which is used to track appointments.
    AppointmentController
    This class is a controller for the Appointment FXML and contains methods to add or modify Appointments.
    Contact
    This class creates a Contract object, which is used to utilize the contacts in the database.
    CountReportingController
    This class is a controller for the CountReporting FXML, and fills a table with data from the Total objects.
    Country
    This class contains the Countries in the database, as well as methods for handling them.
    Customer
    This class is for the Customer objects, which handles the data associated with customers and provides methods for interacting with them.
    CustomerController
    This is the Controller for the Customer FXML, and provides methods to add or modify a Customer.
    DBConnect
    This class contains methods for controlling the connection to the database.
    DBHomeController
    This class is the Controller for the main screen of the program, and has methods to handle all sorts of choices the user could make.
    FirstLevelDivision
    This class creates the First Level Division Object which represents states or provinces.
    Main
    This is the main class of the program.
    PreparedStatements
    This class has all prepared statements used to modify the database.
    ScheduleReportingController
    This class runs the report that shows the schedule for a selected contact.
    SetupDatabaseData
    This class runs statements for initial setup from the database.
    SignInController
    This class is a Controller that is loaded on startup, and allows the user to log in.
    Total
    This class creates the Total object for usage to track Appointment totals.
    User
    This class creates the User object and contains methods to handle them.
